# Backend Architecture (DDD)

## Domain Organization
- Organize backend by domains: e.g., user, resume, billing.
- Each domain encapsulates logic, models, and services.

## Domain Structure
Each domain may contain:
- entities
- value-objects
- services
- repositories
- types/schemas

## Controllers / API Layer
- Handle request/response, validation.
- Call domain services only.
- No business logic in controllers.

## Domain Services
- Contain business rules.
- Coordinate entities.
- Remain independent and testable.

## Data Access
- Database access isolated in repositories.
- Services call repositories; controllers never access DB directly.

## Validation & Security
- Validate all inputs.
- Enforce auth checks.
- Sanitize external inputs.

## Scalability & Maintainability
- Loose coupling between domains.
- Domains evolve independently.
- Replace deprecated APIs or libraries.
